Summary: saw on image after photo was taken
divs: Sighting DetailsMy wife took a photo with her Nikon D5000 out of our hotel room in Toronto. Only later did we notice what appears to be very bright two light orbs with halos and one smaller spherical object above them. I thought maybe the lights were from a plane, although they seem way too bright against a sunset sky to be plane headlights, and the small orb above and slightly to the left appears almost perfectly spherical and doesn't look like a plane at all, to me. Any information on what the researchers here think these objects might be would be welcome.
